A man sells face masks for use to curb the spread of coronavirus outside a makeshift shop in Harare, Zimbabwe. Photographer: Tsvangirayi Mukwazhi/AP Photo Photographer: Tsvangirayi Mukwazhi/AP Photo Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter Zimbabwe has suspended most parliamentary business after two lawmakers and two other people tested positive for the coronavirus. “Two members of parliament had been confirmed positive,” parliamentary Clerk Kenneth Chokuda said in an emailed statement. The two were in a team conducting field visits around the country. A driver and a journalist also contracted the virus, he said.